  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(67) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then did they spit in his face.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—We learn from St. Mark (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:65",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and St. Luke (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:63",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") that these acts of outrage were perpetrated, not by the members of the Sanhedrin, but by the officers who had the accused in their custody, and who, it would seem, availed themselves of the interval between the two meetings of the council to indulge in this wanton cruelty. Here, also, they were unconsciously working out a complete correspondence with Isaiah’s picture of the righteous sufferer (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The word “buffeted” describes a blow with the clenched fist, as contrasted with one with the open palm.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Matthew 26:67-68",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
