      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And buffeted him - That is, they struck him with their hands closed, or with the fist.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Others smote him with the palms of their hands - The word used in the original here means literally to strike with rods. It also means to strike the mouth with the open hand, as if to prevent a person's speaking, or to evince abhorrence of what he had spoken. ",
        "children": [
          {
